TY  - JOUR
T1  - What Went Wrong?
AU  - Eisner, Robert
Y1  - 1971/05/01
PY  - 1971
DA  - 1971/05/01
N1  - doi: 10.1086/259772
DO  - 10.1086/259772
T2  - Journal of Political Economy
JF  - Journal of Political Economy
SP  - 629
EP  - 641
VL  - 79
IS  - 3
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - Failure to stop war-induced inflation is traced to: (1) higher tax rates inducing higher government expenditures; (2) limitations of countercyclical tax changes predictable from the permanent-income hypothesis; (3) perverse effects of certain tax changes on investment demand; (4) tax increases, especially but not exclusively of the excise variety, which raise prices by reducing supply; (5) a liquidity leak, analogous to the liquidity trap, which sharply limits the impact of tight money; (6) inelastic interest-rate expectations which limit real long-term movements, while permanent changes in long rates rule out intertemporal substitution effects; (7) the cost element in higher interest charges, which raises supply prices; (8) possibly decreasing elasticity of lower demand in an imperfectly competitive world; and (9) lags which may be variable as well as long.
AB  - Failure to stop war-induced inflation is traced to: (1) higher tax rates inducing higher government expenditures; (2) limitations of countercyclical tax changes predictable from the permanent-income hypothesis; (3) perverse effects of certain tax changes on investment demand; (4) tax increases, especially but not exclusively of the excise variety, which raise prices by reducing supply; (5) a liquidity leak, analogous to the liquidity trap, which sharply limits the impact of tight money; (6) inelastic interest-rate expectations which limit real long-term movements, while permanent changes in long rates rule out intertemporal substitution effects; (7) the cost element in higher interest charges, which raises supply prices; (8) possibly decreasing elasticity of lower demand in an imperfectly competitive world; and (9) lags which may be variable as well as long.
SN  - 0022-3808
M3  - doi: 10.1086/259772
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1086/259772
Y2  - 2024/03/22
