VL  - 79
IS  - 3
PB  - The University of Chicago Press
N2  - It has been shown that, in the Patinkin model--where real balances appear in the utility function--the traditional Slutsky results are lost. Here, it is argued that work by Baumol, Tobin, Patinkin, and others implies that the utility function is separable in a specific way. It is then shown that, if the utility function is separable in that way, then the traditional Slutsky results are reinstated.
